OL,5, Bereavement payments should be made to 
OL,6, relatives of people killed during the  
OL,7, Troubles, including those who were     
OL,8, paramilitaries, it has been proposed.  
OL,10,FThe suggestion is contained in an      
OL,11,Fadvice paper from the Commission for   
OL,12,FVictims and Survivors sent to the      
OL,13,FExecutive Office at Stormont.          
OL,15,FIf acted upon, about 13,000 people     
OL,16,Fcould benefit.                         
OL,18,FNo amount is suggested, but figures    
OL,19,Fcontained in the paper show the scheme 
OL,20,Fcould cost upwards of #130m.           
